===Etymology===
{{PIE root|nl|kerp}}
From {{inh|nl|odt|*hervist}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*harbistaz}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|nl}} {{m|ine-pro|*kerp-}}. Cognate with High German {{term|Herbst|lang=de}}, Low German {{term|Harvst|lang=nds}}, West Frisian {{term|hjerst|lang=fy}}, English {{term|harvest|lang=en}}; further with Latin {{term|carpere||to [[pick]], to [[pluck]]|lang=la}}, Greek {{term|καρπός||fruit, harvest|lang=grc}}. The original meaning was ‘harvest time’, as is seen in {{term|herfstmaand|lang=nl}}.

